More Inſtances may be collected from almoſt every Chapter by the Judicious, to convince him that not Dr. Gauden but the King was the Author of that Book: I ſuppoſe therefore that the King might inſert that Anſwer after he had given it to the Commiſſioners at the Treaty, for evident it is, that the Title was altered after the Book was in the Preſs by the King's order, on Dr. Taylor's Letter, which is another good Argument. That Dr. Gauden's ſhewing the Title (
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  ) to evade the Fault of impoſing a Book of his own on the Nation in the King's Name, was a meer Fiction of Dr. Walker's; for the Book which was ſent to the Preſs had another Title, viz. Suſpiria Regalia: or, The Royal Defence; and was not altered until the Book was begun to be printed.
